      <h1> Coccidiosis </h1>
      <p> Coccidiosis is a parasitic disease in the intestinal tract of alpacas. </p>
      <br>
      <h2> Causes </h2>
      <p> Coccidiosis is caused by Eimeria protozoa. </p>
      <h2> Common Targets </h2>
      <p> Coccidiosis often affect young Crias </p>
      <h2> Symptoms </h2>
      <p> See your veteranarian for treatment if your camelid has the following symptoms </p>
      <ul>
          <li> Hunched Posture </li>
          <li> Discomfort when moving </li>
          <li> Legs are splayyed and walking slowly </li>
      </ul>
      <h2> Treatment </h2>
      <p> Coccidiosis can be treated with Amprolium or Sulfadimethorine. If severe, use Toltazuril. </p>
